  "doc_id": "37125",
  "text": "Somatic copy-number analysis on the AA CRC and TCGA CRC WES datasets was performed using the developer's recommended parameters for processing WES data from matched tumor/normal samples [CITATION_1] . The window size was set to 500 bp with a step of 250 bp for all of the analyses. GC content normalization was enabled for all of the analyses, along with the noisyData option set as TRUE in order to avoid false-positive predictions due to non-uniform capture in exome sequencing data. For the primary analyses, Control-FREEC (version 6.7) was run in the default mode without enabling correction for contamination by normal cells. However, contamination adjustment was subsequently enabled to evaluate whether automatic inference of tumor content in the tissue samples improved the performance of Control-FREEC.",
